{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-21","name":"Wischard Ledet","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Wischard Ledet","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Wischard"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Ledet"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1164–1222","fullLifespan":"Abt 1164–Bef 4 February 1222","birthDate":"+1164","birthPlace":{"address":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","geo":{"latitude":52.1367,"longitude":-1.2725,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathPlace":{"address":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England","geo":{"latitude":52.1367,"longitude":-1.2725,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nWischard Ledet held the honour of Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire.\n\nWischard Ledet was married to Margaret.\n\nWischard and Margaret were the parents of Christiana Ledet, their heir, who was married to Henry of Braybrooke.\n\nOn 28 May, 1220, \"Northamptonshire. Wischard Ledet gives the king a palfrey for having a weekly market on Tuesdays at his manor of Warden, unless the market etc.\"\n\nOn 4 February, 1222, \"To the sheriff of Northamptonshire. Henry of Braybrooke and Christiana, his wife, daughter and heiress of Wischard Ledet and Margaret, his wife, have made fine to the king by £100 for their relief of the lands formerly of Wischard and Margaret, falling to Christiana by inheritance, which they ought to hold of the king in chief, and the king has taken the homage of Henry. Order that, having accepted security from Henry and Christiana for rendering the aforesaid £100 to the king, he is to cause them to have full seisin of all lands formerly of Wischard and Margaret in Burton and Warden with their appurtenances that fall to Christiana by inheritance.\"\n\nOn 8 September, 55 Henry III [1271], a writ regarding Christiana Ledet, late the wife of Henry [Ledet] instigated an Inquisition on Monday before St Mark the Evangelist, 56 Henry III [1272], [defective], which found Wyscard their son was  the next heir of the said Henry and Christiana, and the said Wyscard begot a son named W(al ?) ... firstborn begot two daughters who are next heirs of the said Henry and Christiana Ledet ... and Christiana the younger, aged 15; and Christiana held in Bedford:\n\nSutton and Potton manors, held of Sir Robert [de Brus]. The manor of Sutton was held of the predecessors of the said Robert de Brus, and one Wyscard Ledet held the said ... Robert de Braybroc, and he freed the manor of Sutton from Jewry and gave it to Henry his son and Christiana daughter of the said ... and it is defended for ½ knight's fee against the lords of the fee; and the manor of Potton is held of the same fee by ex(change) ... for Badewe and Toteham in co. Hertford (sic); and the said manors of Sutton and Potton are united.\n\nCadebury manor, held by the said Christiana in dower of the barony of Eton; and she was dowered by Wyscard her son.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1164","date":"Abt 1164","place":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1198","date":"1198","place":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","type":"Spousal","age":"34","id":"GC98-WHL"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1199","date":"about 1199","place":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England","age":"35","id":"L62P-74S"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1208","date":"1208","place":"West Langton, Leicestershire, England","age":"44","id":"GWY9-29P"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1222","date":"1222","place":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England","age":"58","id":"GC98-WHL"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1222","date":"Bef 4 February 1222","place":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England","age":"58"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","type":"Parental"}],"parent":[{"name":"Wischard Ledet","gender":