ershire, England":"West Langton, Leicestershire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ledet","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Cecile, Emile, Leonce, Angelle, Antoine, Aurelie, Camille, Etienne, Ferrel, Gillis, Gisele.","French: variant of <b>Ledé</b>, from <i>le dé</i>, meaning either ‘the thimble’ or ‘the die’, hence used as a metonymic occupational name for a stitcher or tailor, or as a nickname for a gambler. Compare   Leday   1 and   Ledee   2.","History: Antoine Livaudais Ledet from La Rochelle in Charente-Maritime, France, married first Marguerite Willig in Edgard, LA, in 1788, and second Victoire-Françoise Quimine in Plattenville, LA, in 1797."],"variants":[{"name":"Ledee","meanings":["French (<b>Ledée</b> and <b>Lédée</b>): variant of <b>Ledé</b> (see   Ledet  ). This surname is also found in the West Indies, including Puerto Rico.","Altered form of French   Ledet  ."]},{"name":"Leday","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alcide.","Americanized form of French   Ledet  . This surname is found mainly in LA and TX, and is borne mainly by African Americans. Compare   Lada   5.","In some cases possibly also French: variant, with fused masculine definite article <i>le</i>, of   Day  , a habitatonal name from Day in the Ardennes."]}]},{"name":"Wischard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Wishart  . This surname is very rare in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Wishart","meanings":["The same with the old name Guiscard, in Hebrew R. Wiscard; from Old German wtsa-hart, strong leader. It is found Latinised Guiscardus."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":51,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Wischard Ledet was born about 1164, in Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Wischard Ledet, was 29 and his mother, Christian Longstone, was 25. He married Margaret Foliot in 1198, in Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died before 4 February 1222, in Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England."},"et":{"Abt 1164–Bef 4 February 1222":"umbes 1164–enne 4. veebruari 1222","1164–1222":"1164–1222","1166–Female":"1166–Surnud","1168–1222":"1168–1222","1199–1271":"1199–1271","1136–1208":"1136–1208","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1198":"1198","1164":"1164","1140":"1140","1271":"1271","Abt 1164":"umbes 1164","1215":"1215","1136":"1136","1168":"1168","1222":"1222","1199":"1199","1166":"1166","Bef 4 February 1222":"enne 4. veebruari 1222","about 1199":"umbes 1199","1208":"1208","Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England":"Chipping Warden, Northamptonshire, England","West Langton, Leicestershire, England":"West Langton, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1164–Bef 4 February 1222":"noin 1164–ennen vuotta 4. helmikuuta 1222","1164–1222":"1164–1222","1166–Female":"1166–Kuollut","1168–1222":"1168–1222","1199–1271":"1199–1271","1136–1208":"1136–1208","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1198":"1198","1164":"1164","1140":"1140","1271":"1271","Abt 1164":"noin 1164","1215":"1215","1136":"1136","1168":"1168","1222":"1222","1199":"1199","1166":"1166","Bef 4 February 1222":"ennen vuotta 4. helmikuuta 